Starting with JIRA 6.2.1, a new table was added to manage the Global Permissions in JIRA, the _globalpermissionentry_ table.

This table is used in the place of the schemepermissions table so we need to update our [Retrieving the JIRA Administrator|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA062/Retrieving+the+JIRA+Administrator] in the correct versions to match how JIRA works now.

Here are the changes I found.
# Change from {code:SQL}select perm_parameter from schemepermissions where PERMISSION=0;{code} to {code:SQL}select group_id from globalpermissionentry where PERMISSION='ADMINISTER';{code}
# Change from {code:SQL}select perm_parameter from schemepermissions where PERMISSION=44;{code} to {code:SQL}select group_id from globalpermissionentry where PERMISSION='SYSTEM_ADMIN';{code}
# Change from {code:SQL}update schemepermissions set perm_parameter='jira-system-administrators' where permission=44;
update schemepermissions set perm_parameter='jira-administrators' where permission=0;
update schemepermissions set perm_parameter='jira-users' where permission=1;{code} to {code:SQL}update globalpermissionentry set group_id='jira-system-administrators' where permission='SYSTEM_ADMIN';
update globalpermissionentry set group_id='jira-administrators' where permission='ADMINISTER';
update globalpermissionentry set group_id='jira-users' where permission='USE';{code}
# Change from {code:SQL}insert into schemepermissions (id, scheme, permission, perm_type, perm_parameter) values (444444,NULL,44,'group','jira-administrators');
insert into schemepermissions (id, scheme, permission, perm_type, perm_parameter) values (333333,NULL,1,'group','jira-users');{code} to {code:SQL}insert into globalpermissionentry (id, permission, group_id) values (555555,'SYSTEM_ADMIN','jira-administrators');
insert into globalpermissionentry (id, permission, group_id) values (444444,'ADMINISTER','jira-administrators');
insert into globalpermissionentry (id, permission, group_id) values (333333,'USE','jira-users');{code}

