* Currently JIRA does not log Active Object data restoration progress by default. JIRA by default log progress up to 90% :
{code}
2014-12-18 09:46:29,901 JiraImportTaskExecutionThread-1 INFO admin 583x102x1 1wgfbkt 139.149.181.160 /secure/admin/XmlRestore.jspa [jira.bc.dataimport.DefaultDataImportService] Importing data is 90% complete...
2014-12-18 09:46:32,175 JiraImportTaskExecutionThread-1 INFO admin 583x102x1 1wgfbkt 139.149.181.160 /secure/admin/XmlRestore.jspa [jira.bc.dataimport.DefaultDataImportService] Finished storing Generic Values.
{code}
90% is the indicator of entities.xml was completely restore. From the default JIRA logging, we can't determine if the activeobjects.xml is restored successfully or not. 
(i) We can see the progress on the restoration for Active Object data if we set the Default package to DEBUG before restoring the JIRA XML data.
(i) Suggestion: when JIRA restoring active object, it should also log it instead of 
* Eg: in a situation that JIRA does not have sufficient resource to run the re-indexing after the restoration, instead of throwing error like "Executor has been shutdown" which is very generic, should have clear indicator that the restoration was completed and clear message that the re-index was failing.

